+     throwing on the first such error — then aborts EVERY receive pass at the
+     dead socket, so the newest (hopped) socket, where the roamed server's
+     replies actually arrive later in the deque, is never read: input flows
+     out, nothing ever displays. Instead, skip a dead OLD socket and prune it
